# Winemaker project context

Android (Flutter) app that guides the user step-by-step through making wine.

## Domain glossary

- **Recipe**: an ordered list of **Tasks**. For now only built-in default
  recipes exist (currently one: Red Wine). Custom user recipes are future work.
- **Task**: a single step in a recipe. Has a `TaskType` that decides its screen
  and behavior. Tasks can repeat in a recipe (e.g. `addingIngredients` appears
  2-3 times) and some depend on earlier ones (calculation needs the setup data).
- **Realization**: a started recipe (an instance the user is working through).
  Tracks which recipe, current position, start time, and the data the user
  entered per task. A realization can be in progress or completed.

## Task types

- **setup**: merged step combining desired-wine input + must measurements +
  ingredient calculation on ONE screen (3 sections). These were previously three
  separate tasks but are highly coupled and usually done in one sitting.
  - desired wine: target sweetness + alcohol level.
  - must measurements: collected juice volume, sweetness (Blg), acidity.
  - calculation: from desired wine + measurements, computes which/how many
    ingredients to add (sugar kg, water l, yeast, nutrients).
- **description**: text instructions; user just confirms they did it.
- **addingIngredients**: tells user to add ingredients and shows how much is
  still remaining vs the calculated total. Sugar is usually split into 2-3
  portions (sugar has a per-step limit), so this task repeats; remaining =
  calculated total minus what was already added in prior portions.
- **timeNotification**: a waiting period. Params: description (what we wait for),
  notification delay, postpone time. Sends a push notification after the delay;
  the notification has a "postpone {postpone time} days" button that reschedules
  it. User can also manually complete it early (override the wait).
- **result**: user inputs free text describing results and mistakes. Mainly read
  back later for inspection.

## App flow

1. **Realizations screen** (home/first screen): lists the user's realizations
   ordered by start time. Completed ones are marked and sorted to the bottom.
   From here the user can:
   - open an existing realization (in progress or completed),
   - create a new realization (pick a recipe),
   - go to the **Recipes screen**,
   - go to the **Calculator screen**.
2. **Recipes screen**: browse/inspect built-in recipes (their ordered task
   lists). Adding custom recipes is future work.
3. **Calculator screen**: standalone version of the setup calculation, NOT tied
   to a realization. Enter must measurements + desired wine, get the required
   ingredients. Quick what-if tool.
4. **Realization (recipe) screen**: shows progress (completed + remaining tasks)
   and lets the user work through tasks.

## Realization behavior rules

- User can jump back to any earlier task and redo from there.
- Going back DISCARDS data of all tasks after that point (progress resets to that
  task; later entered data is cleared). This is intentional.
- Any task can be completed immediately as an override (skip waits, confirm
  without redoing work) so fixing earlier mistakes doesn't force re-waiting.
- Completed tasks (before the current pointer) are viewable read-only: grayed
  out, no edit, just inspect the entered values.
- A realization is auto-completed when its final task is completed.
- A completed realization stays in the list; it can be inspected (especially the
  `result` task) or restarted by going back to a selected task (same discard
  rule applies).

## Default recipe: Red Wine

Ordered tasks:
1. description: collect fruits, put in fermentation bucket, squash, take measurements
2. setup (desired wine + must measurements + calculation)
3. addingIngredients: yeast, nutrients, sugar, water
4. timeNotification: ferment in bucket with fruit skins, ~2 weeks, warm room
5. description: squeeze the mass, move to glass fermentation bottle, warm room
6. timeNotification: wait for sugar level to drop, ~2 weeks
7. addingIngredients: remaining sugar
8. timeNotification: wait for fermentation to slow down a lot
9. description: rack the wine to another bottle, discard sediment, cool room
10. timeNotification: a few months
11. description: rack the wine to another bottle, discard sediment, cool room
12. timeNotification: a few months
13. description: pour into bottles, discard sediment
14. result

## Architecture & conventions

- State management: Riverpod 2 (codegen `@riverpod`). Controllers expose
  `AsyncValue`; data access via per-feature repositories over Drift 2.
- Routing: `go_router`; `realizationId` passed as a path param.
- UI: Material 3, light + dark theme.
- Feature-based layout: `lib/features/<feature>/{domain,data,presentation}`;
  `lib/app/` for router/theme/app; `lib/core/` for shared models, constants, and
  the Drift database.
- Task progress and per-task realization data live in ONE unified
  `realization_task_state` table `(realizationId, taskIndex, status, payload)`,
  where `payload` is per-task-type JSON. This is the single source of task state
  and supports repeatable tasks, jump-back-discard (delete rows with
  `taskIndex > N`), and read-only inspection. Do NOT add per-feature singleton
  tables for task data.
- Follow the Flutter rules in `rules.mdc` (no behavior duplication here).
- Platform scope: Android only. No backend/cloud, no auth/multi-user.
